President Obama will be honoring educators from across the country for their excellence in mathematics and science teaching and mentoring at the second event of his "Educate to Innovate" Campaign. The President will also announce new partnerships aimed at helping American students improve their science and math achievement over the next decade. These partnerships involve leading companies, foundations, non-profit organizations, and science and engineering societies. The event will be webcasted and is open to the press. Interested reporters should email their information to media_affairs@who.eop.gov to attend. Over 80 teachers and 20 mentors will be recognized at the event.